## Connection Types

| Type | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `requires` | Pattern A needs Pattern B to function |
| `enables` | Pattern A creates conditions for Pattern B |
| `modifies` | Pattern A changes the behavior of Pattern B |
| `invokes` | Pattern A triggers Pattern B during execution |
| `constrains` | Pattern A limits how Pattern B can operate |

